resource.name: SpecificationLibrary
resource.title: Specification Library
resource.description: A Library that is the package manifest for the Electronic Reporting and Surveillance Distribution (eRSD) 3rd Edition. It defines the components and dependencies that make up an eRSD specification version including reporting parameters, a Reportable Trigger Codes (RCTC) Library of the trigger code value sets, and the trigger code value sets themselves.

expression.expression: (%encounterStartDate + 1 day * %normalReportingDuration >= now()) and (%conditions.exists() or %encounterDiagnoses.exists() or %diagnosticOrders.exists() or %diagnosticResultValues.exists() or %diagnosticResults.exists() or %encounters.exists() or %labOrders.exists() or %labTests.exists() or %labResults.exists() or %labResultValues.exists())

valueExpression.expression: Most recent eICR sent over 72 hours ago?
Is Encounter In Progress and Within Normal Reporting Duration or 72h or less after end of encounter?

expression.expression: %inprogressencounter.where((status = 'in-progress' or status = 'arrived') and %encounterStartDate + 1 day * %normalReportingDuration >= now() or (status = 'finished' and %encounterEndDate + 72 hours >= now())).exists() and %inprogressencounter.where(class.code='IMP' or class.code='EMER' or class.code='OBSENC').exists()

valueExpression.expression: Is Ambulatory Encounter In Progress and Within Ambulatory Reporting Duration or 72h or less after end of encounter?

expression.expression: %ambinprogressencounter.where((status = 'in-progress' or status = 'arrived') and %encounterStartDate + 1 day * %ambulatoryReportingDuration >= now() or (status = 'finished' and %encounterEndDate + 72 hours >= now())).exists() and %ambinprogressencounter.where(class.code='AMB' or class.code='VR' or class.code='HH').exists()

%termencounter.where(((status = 'in-progress' or status = 'arrived') and %encounterStartDate + 1 day * %normalReportingDuration < now()) or (status = 'finished' and %encounterEndDate + 72 hours < now())).exists() and %termencounter.where(class.code='IMP' or class.code='EMER' or class.code='OBSENC').exists()

%termambencounter.where(((status = 'in-progress' or status = 'arrived') and %encounterStartDate + 1 day * %ambulatoryReportingDuration < now()) or (status = 'finished' and %encounterEndDate + 72 hours < now())).exists() and %termambencounter.where(class.code='AMB' or class.code='VR' or class.code='HH').exists()

resource.name: Diagnosis_ProblemTriggersforPublicHealthReporting
resource.title: Diagnosis_Problem Triggers for Public Health Reporting
resource.description: Purpose: Clinical Focus - This set of values contains diagnoses or problems that represent that the patient may have a potentially reportable condition. For example, these may be diagnoses recorded in an EHR problem list and diagnosis codes used for billing for the encounter. Purpose: Data Element Scope - Diagnoses or problems documented in a clinical record. Purpose: Inclusion Criteria - See individual value sets. Purpose: Exclusion Criteria - See individual value sets. Note - Includes codes from selected value sets used in the Reportable Condition Knowledge Management System (RCKMS) reporting logic. RCKMS value sets in VSAC are for informational use only. When implementing trigger codes for electronic case reporting, use the Reportable Condition Trigger Codes (RCTC) file.
resource.purpose: Diagnoses or problems documented in a clinical record.
